(16, '4806426002', '23andMe', 'Scientist / Sr. Manager, Downstream Development - CMC', 'Therapeutics', 'South San Francisco, California', 'http://platform_1.com/jobs/4806426002', 'http://public-logo.com/23andme', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;Since 2006, 23andMeâ€™s mission has been to help people access, understand, and benefit from the human genome. We are a group of passionate individuals pushing the boundaries of whatâ€™s possible to help turn genetic insight into better health and personal understanding.&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Our Therapeutics team, which was established more than five years ago, has been actively &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;identifying novel drug targets using &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;23andMeâ€™s unparalleled database &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;and developing a portfolio across several therapeutic areas, including oncology, cardiovascular and metabolic disease.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a highly motivated Scientist / Senior Manager to join our expanding Therapeutics team. You will lead the CMC downstream process design, development and validation and work together with multiple cross-functional project teams to support product manufacturing and regulatory filing.&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;More information about our Therapeutics team is available&amp;nbsp;at&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://therapeutics.23andme.com/&quot;&gt;https://therapeutics.23andme.com/&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What youâ€™ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;ul&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Oversee and coordinate the CMC downstream process development including chromatography capture steps, viral clearance strategies, polishing&amp;nbsp;operations, and filtrations/concentration/formulatio