(17, '4733785002', '23andMe', 'Senior Cloud Infrastructure Engineer', 'Security', 'Headquarters - Sunnyvale', 'http://platform_1.com/jobs/4733785002', 'http://public-logo.com/23andme', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;23andMe is looking for an experienced Senior Cloud Infrastructure Engineer to join our Security team. You will be responsible for building and maintaining the cloud infrastructure used for massive genetic data science and computation. In this role, you will have a chance to work closely with researchers and scientists to understand how they are using the compute environments and come up with creative solutions to help improve on it.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Since 2006, 23andMeâ€™s mission has been to help people access, understand, and benefit from&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;the human genome.&amp;nbsp; We are a group of passionate individuals pushing the boundaries of whatâ€™s possible to help turn genetic insight into better health and personal understanding.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you&#39;ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;ul&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Build AWS multi-account environments to support high performance computations&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Interface directly with researchers and therapeutics staff to design and tune workloads&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Support the use of bioinformatics and computational packages; including R, Python, Jupyter Notebooks, and batch processing pipelines&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Develop and support scientists environments handling sensitive customer data&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Work directly with AWS architects and other infrastructure engineers to develop and maintain scalable and reproducible infrastructure&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you&#39;ll bring&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;ul&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;5 years of experience in Security Engineering, DevOps or IT Operations roles, strong familiarity with the principles of DevOps or Agile development&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;2 years of hands-on experience securing cloud applications and infrastructure (AWS strongly preferred)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Experience with Infrastructure as Code&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Strong familiarity with continuous integration and continuous deployment&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Familiarity with building and maintaining containers&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Handy with Python, Shell Scripts, Makefiles, etc.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Bonus: Experience with Cloudcustodian or other AWS auto-remediation platforms&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Proven focus on teamwork and collaborative interaction with operations and development teams and other departments.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Ability to present ideas in business-friendly and user-friendly language.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Can-do attitude, motivation and ability to prioritize and execute tasks with minimal supervision.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;23andMe, Inc. is the leading consumer genetics and research company. Founded in 2006, the mission of the company is to help people access, understand, and benefit from the human genome. The company was named by Glassdoor as one of the Best Places to Work in 2019, MIT Technology Review to its â€œ50 Smartest Companies, 2017â€ list, and named one of Fast Companyâ€™s â€œ25 Brands That Matter Now, 2017â€. 23andMe has millions of customers worldwide, with more than 80 percent of customers consented to participate in research. 23andMe, Inc. is located in Sunnyvale, CA. More information is available at &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.23andme.com/&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;www.23andMe.com&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;At 23andMe, we value a diverse, inclusive workforce and we provide equal employment opportunity for all applicants and employees. All qualified applicants for employment will be considered without regard to an individualâ€™s race, color, sex, gender identity, gender expression, religion, age, national origin or ancestry, citizenship, physical or mental disability, medical condition, family care status, marital status, domestic partner status, sexual orientation, genetic information, military or veteran status, or any other basis protected by federal, state or local laws.&amp;nbsp; If you are unable to submit your application because of incompatible assistive technology or a disability, please contact us at &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;accommodations-ext@23andme.com&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;. 23andMe will reasonably accommodate qualified individuals with disabilities to the extent required by applicable law.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Please note: 23andMe does not accept agency resumes and we are not responsible for any fees related to unsolicited resumes. Thank you.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', '2020-08-04 13:15:09'),
(18, '4738022002', '23andMe', 'Senior Privacy Counsel', 'Legal and Regulatory Affairs', 'Sunnyvale, CA', 'http://platform_1.com/jobs/4738022002', 'https://benti-energies.com/asset/images/clients/logo-default.svg', '&lt;div&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;23andMe is focused on maintaining its trusted position with regard to genetic information and data stewardship, including health information contributed by customers. We believe that the customer data we hold belongs to them - our customers, and that we must act as a responsible steward of that data.&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Since 2006, 23andMeâ€™s mission has been to help people access, understand, and benefit from the human genome. We are a group of passionate individuals pushing the boundaries of whatâ€™s possible to help turn genetic insight into better health and personal understanding.&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What youâ€™ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;With a thorough understanding of 23andMeâ€™s business and strategic priorities, you will identify the implications of product, marketing, research and other initiatives on privacy and data use, technology architecture and standards and data governance, to ensure 23andMe maintains its focus on transparency and leadership in privacy and data protection. You will support the continued growth of 23andMeâ€™s comprehensive privacy and data protection program, including conducting education and training at all levels of the company. You will be a key player in leading privacy strategies, be an integral cross-functional team player, work closely with internal and external parties on compliance, policy and government affairs matters.&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;ul&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with Security, IT, product and other business teams to develop, implement, oversee and monitor 23andMeâ€™s privacy and data protection policies and procedures.&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Assess how current and proposed laws impact business processes, reporting, record keeping, or other activities. Identify needs for introduction of new business processes and for consultations or training.&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Lead cross-functional projects related to data governance, data protection and privacy by design.&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Lead vendor management program, including responsibility for creating policies, processes and templates to support transactions.&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Ensure 23andMe privacy policies and practices are included in development of product offerings and business processes including, marketing, market research, customer support, and other operational mechanisms and performance measures.&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Develop strategies, tools, resources and frameworks enabling data use innovation while ensuring adherence to privacy best practices.&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Together with Security, lead privacy and data protection risk assessments/audits and monitoring to identify opportunities, issues and risks and develop appropriate mitigation plans in support of company risk management and internal audit deliverables.&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Serve on data incident response and resolution teams; work across the organization to assess incidents and determine appropriate response.&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Represent the organizationâ€™s privacy and data protection interests with external parties.&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Provide leadership for the Privacy team.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What youâ€™ll bring&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;JD with excellent academic credentials.&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Member of the California bar.&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;+6 years of privacy experience in a law firm, in-house or other legal role with a track record of providing practical business-friendly advice.&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;CIPP/US/E certification preferred.&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Expert knowledge of data protection and information security laws, rules and regulations in the US and globally, including CCPA, GDPR,&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Genetic Information Nondiscrimination Act, FCRA, HIPAA, COPPA, and relevant rules and regulatory guidance related to mobile applications, as well as industry leading privacy and data protection practices and standards.&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of online and offline advertising and marketing rules and regulations, including state consumer protection statutes, CAN-SPAM,&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Telephone Consumer Protection Act and FTC guidelines pertaining to areas relevant to 23andMeâ€™s business, such as consumer advertising.&lt;br&gt;Knowledge of and experience with data security, data breach, and data loss prevention tools and statutes.&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Experience and skill in responding to press inquiries and speaking on privacy matters.&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated analytical skills as well as the ability to take disparate information and make strategic recommendations quickly.&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Experience with FDA regulatory issues related to privacy, including government requirements for compliance programs preferred.&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated leadership with evidence of increasing management responsibility.&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Ability to develop and deliver presentations to senior management and influence others.&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Exceptional attention to detail and ability to get things done.&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Strong organizational, coordination, multi-tasking, and process improvement capabilities.&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Excellent interpersonal skills, including relationship building and collaboration.&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Excellent verbal and written communicator.&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;23andMe, Inc. is the leading consumer genetics and research company. Founded in 2006, the mission of the company is to help people access, understand, and benefit from the human genome. The company was named by Glassdoor as one of the Best Places to Work in 2019, MIT Technology Review to its â€œ50 Smartest Companies, 2017â€ list, and named one of Fast Companyâ€™s â€œ25 Brands That Matter Now, 2017â€. 23andMe has millions of customers worldwide, with more than 80 percent of customers consented to participate in research. 23andMe, Inc. is located in Sunnyvale, CA. More information is available at &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.23andme.com/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; data-saferedirecturl=&quot;https://www.google.com/url?q=http://www.23andme.com&amp;amp;source=gmail&amp;amp;ust=1588282920841000&amp;amp;usg=AFQjCNHbVZG08c5CWRfM_Ub73PWhCGasDA&quot;&gt;www.23andMe.com&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;At 23andMe, we value a diverse, inclusive workforce and we provide equal employment opportunity for all applicants and employees. All qualified applicants for employment will be considered without regard to an individualâ€™s race, color, sex, gender identity, gender expression, religion, age, national origin or ancestry, citizenship, physical or mental disability, medical condition, family care status, marital status, domestic partner status, sexual orientation, genetic information, military or veteran status, or any other basis protected by federal, state or local laws.&amp;nbsp; If you are unable to submit your application because of incompatible assistive technology or a disability, please contact us at &lt;a href=&quot;mailto:accommodations-ext@23andme.com&quot;&gt;accommodations-ext@23andme.com&lt;/a&gt;. 23andMe will reasonably accommodate qualified individuals with disabilities to the extent required by applicable law.&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;Please note: 23andMe does not accept agency resumes and we are not responsible for any fees related to unsolicited resumes. Thank you.&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;/div&gt;', '2020-08-04 13:15:09'),
(19, '4640766002', '23andMe', 'Sr. Associate Scientist / Scientist I, Antibody Engineering', 'Therapeutics', 'South San Francisco, California', 'http://platform_1.com/jobs/4640766002', 'http://public-logo.com/23andme', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;23andMe, the leading consumer genetics company, has accumulated a wealth of genotypic and phenotypic information from participants committed to improving human health through advances in genomics. Our Therapeutics team uses this data to discover and develop novel medicines to treat important diseases. The team currently has research programs across several therapeutic areas, including oncology, skin, respiratory and cardiovascular disease.&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;We are seeking an outstanding Senior Associate Scientist or Scientist I who will contribute to the generation, characterization and engineering of antibodies across the Therapeutics portfolio.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;For more information about our Therapeutics team, please visit&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://therapeutics.23andme.com/&quot;&gt;https://therapeutics.23andme.com/&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What youâ€™ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;ul&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Execute antibody engineering to improve desired properties for therapeutic development using molecular biology approaches including phage display and mutagenesis&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Perform antibody production, characterization and biochemical / biophysical analysis in high-throughput manner&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Support large-scale antibody sequence and structural model analysis&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Collaborate with therapeutic leads to plan the strategy for antibody discovery and optimization engineering&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Interpret, record and present complex biological data&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Communicate and collaborate with other colleagues&amp;nbsp;effectively&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What youâ€™ll bring&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;ul&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Ph.D. with 2+ years of research experience in molecular biology, protein engineering, antibody engineering, biochemistry, structural biology or related field, or Master&#39;s/Bachelor&#39;s degree with 5+ years of industry experience with proven record of accomplishments and publications.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Strong technical expertise in wide range of molecular biology and protein engineering techniques, including mutagenesis, molecular cloning, construct design, protein expression and purification, protein interaction characterization (ELISA, BIAcore, Octet) and sequence analysis&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Excellent communication and interpersonal skills with an ability to work both independently and in a team environment&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Critical thinking with high degree of innovative and analytical skills&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Note:&amp;nbsp; Job title will be commensurate with experience and academic credentials.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;div&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;23andMe, Inc. is the leading consumer genetics and research company. Founded in 2006, the mission of the company is to help people access, understand, and benefit from the human genome. The company was named by Glassdoor as one of the Best Places to Work in 2019, MIT Technology Review to its â€œ50 Smartest Companies, 2017â€ list, and named one of Fast Companyâ€™s â€œ25 Brands That Matter Now, 2017â€. 23andMe has millions of customers worldwide, with more than 80 percent of customers consented to participate in research. 23andMe, Inc. is located in Sunnyvale, CA. More information is available at &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.23andme.com/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; data-saferedirecturl=&quot;https://www.google.com/url?q=http://www.23andme.com&amp;amp;source=gmail&amp;amp;ust=1588282920841000&amp;amp;usg=AFQjCNHbVZG08c5CWRfM_Ub73PWhCGasDA&quot;&gt;www.23andMe.com&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;At 23andMe, we value a diverse, inclusive workforce and we provide equal employment opportunity for all applicants and employees. All qualified applicants for employment will be considered without regard to an individualâ€™s race, color, sex, gender identity, gender expression, religion, age, national origin or ancestry, citizenship, physical or mental disability, medical condition, family care status, marital status, domestic partner status, sexual orientation, genetic information, military or veteran status, or any other basis protected by federal, state or local laws.&amp;nbsp; If you are unable to submit your application because of incompatible assistive technology or a disability, please contact us at &lt;a href=&quot;mailto:accomodations-ext@23andme.com&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;accomodations-ext@23andme.com&lt;/a&gt;. 23andMe will reasonably accommodate qualified individuals with disabilities to the extent required by applicable law.&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;Please note: 23andMe does not accept agency resumes and we are not responsible for any fees related to unsolicited resumes. Thank you.&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;/div&gt;', '2020-08-04 13:15:09'),
(20, '4748372002', '23andMe', 'Sr. Manager, Consumer Business Development', 'Product', 'Headquarters - Sunnyvale', 'http://platform_1.com/jobs/4748372002', 'http://public-logo.com/23andme', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;23andMe is looking for an exceptional Sr. Manager of Business Development to drive new business opportunities and identify trends and their impact on 23andMeâ€™s business. You will report into the Product organization and be responsible for conducting market landscape research, competitive analysis, reviews of business opportunities, and creation of strategic recommendations, and both internal and external relationship building. Through grit, humility, and persistence, you bring strong interpersonal skills, critical thinking, and sound business judgment, along with the ability to think about what is -- and what could be.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Since 2006, 23andMeâ€™s mission has been to help people access, understand, and benefit from the human genome. We are a group of passionate individuals pushing the boundaries of whatâ€™s possible to help turn genetic insight into better health and personal understanding.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you&#39;ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;\n&lt;ul&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Actively identify, source, and meet with healthcare start-ups to identify trends and source potential partners, either directly or on behalf of the leadership&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Collaborate with the Business Development, Product, Marketing, Legal and Research teams to execute our product business strategy&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Maintain a deep understanding and current awareness of the healthcare industry including digital health&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Structure, negotiate and execute partnering agreements across a broad range of deal structures&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Help define partnership/market requirements, produce qualitative and quantitative analysis of product/program performance, aggregate feedback, explore new strategic opportunities&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n&lt;ul&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Conduct industry and market analyses in support of strategic management decisions, including review of commercial opportunities, market landscape reviews, partner/build/buy analyses and development of executive presentations&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Respond to research requests from the CEO, including company analysis and competitive assessments.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Understand and be a source of critical information on the competitive landscape and industry offerings&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Research and attend relevant industry conferences&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What youâ€™ll bring&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;ul&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;8+ years of experience with business development and partnerships&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Strong knowledge of healthcare industry, including digital health&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Proven ability to plan and manage at both the strategic and operational level and to launch new products successfully in the marketplace.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Experience successfully leading and building strong working relationships with cross-functional teams internally and externally with executives at partner organizations&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Sharp analytical and problem-solving skills, with rigorous attention to detail as well as strategic thinking&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Organized, self-starter, and ability to adjust to quickly changing landscape in consumer genetics&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Advanced degree (PhD, JD, or MBA) preferred.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;23andMe, Inc. is the leading consumer genetics and research company. Founded in 2006, the mission of the company is to help people access, understand, and benefit from the human genome. The company was named by Glassdoor as one of the Best Places to Work in 2019, MIT Technology Review to its â€œ50 Smartest Companies, 2017â€ list, and named one of Fast Companyâ€™s â€œ25 Brands That Matter Now, 2017â€. 23andMe has millions of customers worldwide, with more than 80 percent of customers consented to participate in research. 23andMe, Inc. is located in Sunnyvale, CA. More information is available at&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.23andme.com/&quot;&gt; &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;www.23andMe.com&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;At 23andMe, we value a diverse, inclusive workforce and we provide equal employment opportunity for all applicants and employees. All qualified applicants for employment will be considered without regard to an individualâ€™s race, color, sex, gender identity, gender expression, religion, age, national origin or ancestry, citizenship, physical or mental disability, medical condition, family care status, marital status, domestic partner status, sexual orientation, genetic information, military or veteran status, or any other basis protected by federal, state or local laws.&amp;nbsp; If you are unable to submit your application because of incompatible assistive technology or a disability, please contact us at accommodations-ext@23andme.com. 23andMe will reasonably accommodate qualified individuals with disabilities to the extent required by applicable law.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Please note: 23andMe does not accept agency resumes and we are not responsible for any fees related to unsolicited resumes. Thank you.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', '2020-08-04 13:15:09'),
(21, '4686582002', '23andMe', 'Sr. Manager, Therapeutics Procurement', 'Operations', 'South San Francisco', 'http://platform_1.com/jobs/4686582002', 'http://public-logo.com/23andme', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;23andMe is searching for a talented individual contributor who will drive improvements across all aspects of procurement and Operations.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Since 2006, 23andMeâ€™s mission has been to help people access, understand, and benefit from the human genome. We are a group of passionate individuals pushing the boundaries of whatâ€™s possible to help turn genetic insight into better health and personal understanding.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What youâ€™ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;You will collaborate with multiple cross-functional teams to develop, lead and implement optimal sourcing solutions for 23andMeâ€™s Therapeutics Division. You will be accountable for sourcing of services and goods, material planning, supplier management, and overall supply chain risk reduction and total cost management. The key to your success will be the ability to create and effectively manage procurement business processes and sourcing strategies that enable 23andMe to scale and meet our substantial growth plans. You will also help manage Operational support for 23andMeâ€™s therapeutics needs and participate in new initiatives to drive operational excellence. A successful applicant will be familiar with the third party contractor organizations, sourcing strategies, and activities relevant to key internal partners, including Translational Sciences, specifically Toxicology, Pathology, and Translational PK, Research, both in vitro and in vivo pharmacology, Clinical Sciences, and Chemistry, Manufacturing and Controls.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;If you believe in 23andMe&#39;s mission, have demonstrated success in creating business value across multiple areas within procurement, and provide high levels of service to your business partners we want to speak with you!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What youâ€™ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;ul&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Create, lead, and implement strategies to drive supplier selection, qualification, commercial negotiations, contract development, and contract administration activities.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Exercise sound business judgment and a risk-based review in leveraging and implementing sourcing and procurement activities, including recommendations for alternative solutions that meet business priorities.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Collaborate effectively with key partners in research and development to select supplier and site, contract and quote work, and ensure quality and completion of outsourced activities&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Enable tech transfer of manufacturing and/or assays to external partners with demonstrated expertise and relevant GxP compliance&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Manage supply and delivery of goods and services, to ensure unimpeded operations. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Identify opportunities that focus on cost reductions, efficiencies&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;quality improvements, risk mitigation, industry and supply trends and shifts in technology.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Proactively encourage and foster effective teamwork, and actively solicit ideas from others that are used in seeking sound business solutions.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Manage procurement transactions such as orders, invoices, packing slips, etc.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Become the resident expert in PTP processes and systems and participate in projects focused on improving such processes and systems.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Effectively manage the supply ordering system and catalogs maintained in this portal.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Understand compliance issues and their impacts to the business by ensuring confidentiality/legal/internal controls requirements are being met.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Act with integrity by maintaining compliance with internal policies, procedures and all regulatory and governmental regulations and laws.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Perform other related duties as assigned including but not limited to supporting sourcing projects and supplier management activities in support of other groups within 23andMe.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Help improve operational efficiencies for 23andMeâ€™s Therapeutics division by implementing creative solutions and establishing performance indicators.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Identify and support process improvement initiatives for 23andMe Therapeutics Operations.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What youâ€™ll bring&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;ul&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree required preferably in supply chain management, management sciences, biology, business or finance; advanced degree a plus.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;7-10&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt; y&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;ears of experience in procurement, material requirements planning, Pharmaceutical R&amp;amp;D Operations and/or related supply chain functions, preferably in medical device, therapeutics or other similar regulated industry.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Demonstrated success supporting R&amp;amp;D / laboratory environments and Operational and Outsourced activities.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Strong interpersonal, communication and influencing skills with the ability to see issues from multiple viewpoints and understand the needs of different stakeholders.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Excellent teamwork skills and proven aptitude to partner effectively with a wide range of stakeholders (i.e., colleagues, suppliers, and internal&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;external customers).&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Proven ability to lead cross-functional groups and projects, developing and executing sourcing strategies, contract negotiations and managing 3rd party supplier relationships.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Demonstrated success developing, documenting, implementing and improving business processes.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Work knowledge of GLP, GMP, and GCP and other associated regulations.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Solid understanding or CRO, CMO, CDMO landscape, including capabilities and limitations of vendors and sites worldwide&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Ability to initiate and lead change, work independently, prioritize and multi-task while maintaining a positive and collaborative attitude.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Tenacious attention to detail and consistency.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Experience with an ERP system is required. Familiarity with Oracle NetSuite and Coupa applications highly desired.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Familiarity with general Pharma R&amp;amp;D area, pharma R&amp;amp;D terminology, exposure and experience in Pharma R&amp;amp;D centric procurement support, ability to understand diverse and at times complex Pharma R&amp;amp;D centric procurement needs, vendor management and therapeutics Operations needs and able to translate them into viable scalable solutions.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Demonstrated experience and ability to work with a diverse set of Therapeutics R&amp;amp;D SMEs in Discovery, pre-clinical, Toxicology, Development and CMC as well as Therapeutics leadership and Therapeutics&amp;nbsp; Business Ops team.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Demonstrated experience working with key stakeholders (R&amp;amp;D Finance, Facility, IT, Accounting, Legal/contracts) to help drive procurement and Operational support efforts.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;23andMe, Inc. is the leading consumer genetics and research company. Our mission is to help people access, understand and benefit from the human genome. The company was named by MIT Technology Review to its â€œ50 Smartest Companies, 2017â€ list, and named one of Fast Companyâ€™s â€œ25 Brands That Matter Now, 2017â€. 23andMe has over 5 million customers worldwide, with ~85 percent of customers consented to participate in research. 23andMe is located in Mountain View, CA. More information is available at&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.23andme.com/&quot;&gt; &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;www.23andMe.com&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;At 23andMe, we value a diverse, inclusive workforce and we provide equal employment opportunity for all applicants and employees. All qualified applicants for employment will be considered without regard to an individualâ€™s race, color, sex, gender identity, gender expression, religion, age, national origin or ancestry, citizenship, physical or mental disability, medical condition, family care status, marital status, domestic partner status, sexual orientation, genetic information, military or veteran status, or any other basis protected by federal, state or local laws.&amp;nbsp; If you are unable to submit your application because of incompatible assistive technology or a disability, please contact us at accommodations-ext@23andme.com. 23andMe will reasonably accommodate qualified individuals with disabilities to the extent required by applicable law.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Please note: 23andMe does not accept agency resumes and we are not responsible for any fees related to unsolicited resumes. Thank you.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', '2020-08-04 13:15:09');
