(41, '2269403', '6sense', 'Legal Operations Administrator', 'G&A', 'Remote', 'http://platform_1.com/jobs/2269403', 'http://public-logo.com/6sense', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Legal Operations Administrator &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Company&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;6sense is an innovator in marking and sales enablement.&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/strong&gt;The 6sense Account Based Orchestration Platform helps revenue teams identify and close more opportunities by putting the power of AI, big data and machine learning behind every member of the B2B revenue team, empowering them to uncover anonymous buying behavior, prioritize fragmented data to focus on accounts in market, and engage resistant buying teams with personalized, multi-channel, multi-touch campaigns. 6sense helps revenue teams know everything they need to know about their buyers so they can easily do anything they need to do to generate more opportunities, increase deal size, get into opportunities sooner, compete and win more often.&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp; Our growing legal team is looking for an enthusiastic team player to support and &amp;nbsp;spearhead improvements, processes and communications within the &amp;nbsp;6sense contracting process, as well as work with the Legal Department to implement projects designed to optimize the delivery of legal services. Broadly speaking, this person will have an important role in &amp;nbsp;the continued implementation of operational efficiency within the legal team, freedom to identify key areas of improvement and influence procedures and best legal practices for the Legal Department.&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;ul&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Maintain the legal request tracking system, contracts repository and other tools and systems used by the legal team.&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Triage workload among lawyers and assignments using Smartsheets, Salesforce and other tools, including admin Docusign management.&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Communicate with team members and vendors regarding contract status, process-related questions and feedback from customer facing teams&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Provide front-line support for contract creation and management, such as order forms, SaaS subscription agreements, DPAs and similar customer and vendor facing contracts &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Support data privacy team in data subject management process&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Provide patent system tracking support and coordination&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Assist on additional projects as they arise, including corporate transaction support&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Develop skills in different areas of business and subject matter expertise in Legal Ops &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;ul&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree or equivalent work experience required&lt;br&gt; Minimum 2+ years of direct contract experience in Enterprise Software industry&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with regularly negotiated contract clauses and compliance issues in the Enterprise Software industry a bonus&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Ability to effectively collaborate and influence in a dynamic environment&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Good judgment in working and communicating with clients&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Excellent organizational skills and attention to detail&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Ability to work successfully toward deadlines while re-balancing priorities as needed&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Desire to learn and a curious intellect for the company and industry&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Self-starter with a positive attitude&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;', '2020-08-05 10:59:48'),
(42, '2204411', '6sense', 'OEM Sales Representative', 'Sales', 'San Francisco', 'http://platform_1.com/jobs/2204411', 'http://public-logo.com/6sense', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;OEM Sales Representative &lt;br&gt; San Francisco&lt;br&gt; &lt;br&gt; The Company:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;The 6sense Account Based Orchestration Platform helps revenue teams identify and close more opportunities by putting the power of AI, big data and machine learning behind every member of the B2B revenue team, empowering them to uncover anonymous buying behavior, prioritize fragmented data to focus on accounts in market, and engage resistant buying teams with personalized, multi-channel, multi-touch campaigns. 6sense helps revenue teams know everything they need to know about their buyers so they can easily do anything they need to do to generate more opportunities, increase deal size, get into opportunities sooner, compete and win more often.&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role:&amp;nbsp; &lt;/strong&gt;Imagine how 6sense is tearing up the Account Based Engagement market by predicting with degree of accuracy the companies that are in market to buy; now what if you can connect other channels to use this information effectively to engage those willing buyers. This role will be at the forefront of building out that technology partner ecosystem, responsible for driving the growth of our B2B OEM business. The right candidate will have a history of finding &amp;amp; creating new as well as cultivating existing OEM relationships = a hunter that can farm. Our target partners are makers of B2B software that benefit from company identity of site visitors for effective personalization, mostly from the following markets: software, high-tech, manufacturing, and finance. We are now able to offer similar identity mapping at a company level to SaaS providers that greatly increases the breadth of companies that will benefit from an OEM partnership with 6sense.&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;ul&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Handling a multi-million dollar quota&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Representing the B2B OEM team in their working with other 6sense groups&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;The role may require travelling within US to recruit new OEM business partners and manage existing contracts&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Maintaining and growing an existing account base by developing and implementing a specific growth plan for each account&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;The individual will benefit from coordination with local 6sense field sales operations and leverage other teams for best practices&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Reporting to OEM business management, he/she will need to ensure proper communication at corporate level&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Seeking and adding new accounts that will enhance 6sense&#39;s standing and bottom line&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Seeking and bringing to new product / market opportunities&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Here are the traits you exhibit as a leader:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;ul&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Weâ€™re in the early stages of building our partnership team so weâ€™re looking for people who not only have a&amp;nbsp;track record of being the best of the best, closing big deals and passion for fundamentally changing B2B marketing and sales, but can also think critically about driving growth and building our organization.&amp;nbsp; This is a unique opportunity to help shape and accelerate our success.&lt;br&gt; &lt;br&gt; Here are the traits you exhibit;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Intrinsic drive to be successful, love to win â€“ youâ€™ll take initiative to figure it out, are motivated to do your absolute best work. (Thatâ€™s why youâ€™ve ended up at top across your career.)&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Clear, succinct communicator â€“ Using your customerâ€™s language, youâ€™ll help them clearly understand the value 6sense delivers&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Technical expertise â€“ youâ€™ll demonstrate and speak to&amp;nbsp;how&amp;nbsp;6sense drives success&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Innately curious â€“ youâ€™ll know your buyer, their business, and what 6sense means to their success&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Empathetic listener â€“ youâ€™ll listen more than you talk. And, you really get what they mean&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Collaborate and win as a team â€“ youâ€™ll compete, but above that youâ€™ll collaborate, youâ€™ll share what is working, youâ€™ll help the team win, youâ€™ll take on projects outside of closing deals&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n&lt;ul&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;You will be a proven closer of new business = hunter&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;A creative thinker who knows how to determine a customer&#39;s needs and put together a win-win proposal and carry it through to contract execution&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Competent and experienced in the application of Target Account Selling methodology or other Sales/Business methodologies&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Experience in Martech / Salestech solution space is desirable but not a must&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;ul&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;7+ years of quota carrying software or technology sales, closing complex sales cycles&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;At least 3 years of selling to OEM partners&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Consistent track record of over-achieving quota (top 10-20% of company)&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Experience closing transactions &amp;gt;$250k ACV to line of business executives&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;ul&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Experience selling to Enterprise CMOs, VPs Demand Gen, Marketing Operations, Sales leaders&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with marketing tech landscape such as conversational AI, content hub, personalization, etc.&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Strong and demonstrated written and verbal communications skills&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Ability to work in a fast-paced, team environment&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;4-year BA/BS degree or equivalent practical experience&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Strong C-level customer references&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;', '2020-07-29 12:18:51'),
(43, '2264201', '6sense', 'Partner Manager', 'Sales', 'San Francisco', 'http://platform_1.com/jobs/2264201', 'http://public-logo.com/6sense', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Partner Manager&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;br&gt; &lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Company:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;The 6sense Account Based Orchestration Platform helps revenue teams identify and close more opportunities by putting the power of AI, big data and machine learning behind every member of the B2B revenue team, empowering them to uncover anonymous buying behavior, prioritize fragmented data to focus on accounts in market, and engage resistant buying teams with personalized, multi-channel, multi-touch campaigns. 6sense helps revenue teams know everything they need to know about their buyers so they can easily do anything they need to do to generate more opportunities, increase deal size, get into opportunities sooner, compete and win more often.&lt;br&gt; &lt;br&gt; &lt;strong&gt;The Role:&lt;/strong&gt; As a&amp;nbsp;Partner Manager&amp;nbsp;youâ€™ll be responsible for managing and expanding referral and strategic partner relationships and will have responsibility for the partner sourced and influenced pipeline and bookings number. You will be the primary liaison between the 6sense sales teams and partner organizations, and you will help to build a comprehensive, structured program for training and enabling service partners.&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;You are skilled at building and developing relationships with both internal and external teams. You are a natural connector and communicator who has experience discovering a companyâ€™s goals and then uncovering and facilitating joint solutions. You have a deep understanding of the B2B SaaS ecosystem and have strong relationships with ISVâ€™s, SIâ€™s, and technology integrators alike.&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How youâ€™ll make an impact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;ul&gt;\n&lt;ul&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Work closely with our sales teams to develop pipeline and attach appropriate partners to deals&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Create strong relationships with sales leadership as well as with individual members of the sales team&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Have primary responsibility over the partner sourced and influenced numbers&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Responsible for developing and executing referral and strategic partnerships to contribute to the pipeline numbers&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Identify partnership opportunities by identifying partner prospects&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Develop and execute on a partner pipeline&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Work with and support our partners in referring 6sense platforms&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Manage end-to-end partner relationships&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Ability to face issues that may arise and navigate them using the relationships youâ€™ve developed internally and externally&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Implement strategic communication strategies and materials to advance understanding of 6sense platform with our partners&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Communicate and educate with all levels of partner teams (from executive to implementation) on the 6sense platform&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Deepen relationships with existing partners by looking at opportunities for joint programs&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Maintain 360-degree communication with both internal and external teams&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;ul&gt;\n&lt;ul&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;3 - 5 years of experience in an Alliances, Partnership, Sales, Enterprise Account Management, or Channel role&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Experience engaging and influencing senior executives and strong familiarity with decision-making processes in enterprise customers&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Experience working with partners through account management, product management, program management, and business development engagements&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Excellent verbal and written communications skills are necessary, as well as the ability to work effectively across internal and external organizations&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated experience working and communicating with multiple stakeholders and cross-functional teams including direct and channel marketing, solution architect teams, product management, and account management teams&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Sales and/or technical acumen, able to coordinate and develop successful field teams&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to generate pipeline leveraging partner relationships&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Entrepreneurial, self-starter who can roll up their sleeves or up-level as needed to generate results&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to think ahead, engage proactively and take initiative&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred Experience:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;ul&gt;\n&lt;ul&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Program development and project management experience&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Experience using the Crossbeam account mapping tool&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Prior direct sales experience is preferred&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Any PRM experience&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;', '2020-07-29 12:18:51'),
(44, '2281844', '6sense', 'People Operations- Payroll Coordinator', 'G&A', 'Pune, India', 'http://platform_1.com/jobs/2281844', 'http://public-logo.com/6sense', '&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Title: People Operations/Payroll Coordinator&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;6sense is seeking a People Operations- Payroll Coordinator in its Pune office. 6sense is a Predictive Intelligence Engine that is reimagining how B2B companies do sales and marketing. It works with big data at scale, advanced machine learning and predictive modelling to find buyers and predict what they will purchase, when and how much. By combining intent signals from every channel with the industryâ€™s most advanced AI predictive capabilities, it is finally possible to predict account demand and optimize demand generation in an ABM world.&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;You will join our growing People Operations team to help execute on our HR strategy related to&amp;nbsp; timely and accurate payroll processing and other HR initiatives. The people operations/payroll coordinator is responsible for the transmission of payroll transactions. You will also help with other administrative hr task. We are looking to hire a people operations/ payroll coordinator who is &amp;nbsp;deadline driven, organized, detail oriented, have great written and oral communication skills, with payroll processing and benefits administration experience and has a working knowledge of HR principles, practices and procedures&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Responsibilities:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;ul&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Under the direction of the Payroll Specialist, the Payroll Coordinator is responsible for gathering and input of all required payroll data needed to accurately process a global payroll for exempt and non-exempt employees&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Process requests for paycheck adjustments, commissions, bonuses, retro amounts and final checks, as necessary&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Assist Payroll Specialist with set-up and monitoring of payroll tax registrations&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Perform ad hoc payroll audits to ensure the accuracy of employee data and payroll compliance&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Generate weekly payroll reporting&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Resolve payroll issues&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Providing day-to-day human resources support&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Respond to inbound employee questions regarding benefits, payroll, and company policies&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Stay up to date on US HR laws (payroll, benefits, compliance, terminations, leave of absence ect.)&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;People Operations/Payroll Coordinator Requirements and Qualifications &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;ul&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;2-4 years payroll processing experience for US company with 200+ employees&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Previous experience using Zenefits and ADP payroll processing systems&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Working understanding of human resources principles, practices and procedures&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Understanding of US employment law&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Excellent Collaborator&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Strong skills using Microsoft Office Suite&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Strong communication skills, both oral and written&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Bachelorâ€™s degree in business administration, human resources, finance, accounting or related field preferred&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Desired Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;ul style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Graduates/Postgraduates&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;B.com/MBA Finance (Preferred)&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interpersonal Attributes:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;ul style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Proven analytical skills, strong interpersonal skills&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Be a persistent, creative problem solver&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Good written and verbal communication&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Work independently as well as part of a team&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;', '2020-08-07 06:45:31');
