(51, '2281884', '6sense', 'Senior Human Resources Generalist', 'G&A', 'San Francisco, CA', 'http://platform_1.com/jobs/2281884', 'http://public-logo.com/6sense', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sr. Human Resources Generalist&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;San Francisco, Ca&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;You will join our growing People Operations team and help execute on our HR strategy. You should be deadline driven, organized, detail oriented, have great written and oral communication skills, with project management experience, be a strategic thinker and most importantly personable and approachable.&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a Sr. Human Resources Generalist to join our People Operations Team. In this position you will help coordinate, drive and execute HR programs from original concept through completion, and perform other administrative HR tasks.&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p style=&quot;padding-left: 40px;&quot;&gt;Â· Work directly with the People Operations Team and collaborate on a variety of HR projects&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p style=&quot;padding-left: 40px;&quot;&gt;Â· Coordinate and help create detailed project plans, including progress tracking, monitoring change and ensuring that project deliverables are achieved on time&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p style=&quot;padding-left: 40px;&quot;&gt;Â· Drive and help execute project plan including adoption, scheduling HR program work and coordinate activities of the program to include project communications to broadcast targeted messaging of projects and initiatives&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p style=&quot;padding-left: 40px;&quot;&gt;Â· Respond to inbound employee questions regarding benefits, payroll, and company policies&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p style=&quot;padding-left: 40px;&quot;&gt;Â· Assist in new hire onboarding process, including tracking new hires, employee set up, organizing and scheduling, creating new employee files, ensuring all necessary paperwork is properly filled out and submitted to appropriate persons&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p style=&quot;padding-left: 40px;&quot;&gt;Â· Stay up to date on US HR laws (payroll, benefits, compliance, terminations, leave of absence ect.)&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sr. Human Resources Generalist Requirements and Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p style=&quot;padding-left: 40px;&quot;&gt;Â· HR Project Management Experience&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p style=&quot;padding-left: 40px;&quot;&gt;Â· Ability to handle multiple projects&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p style=&quot;padding-left: 40px;&quot;&gt;Â· Working understanding of human resources principles, practices and procedures&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p style=&quot;padding-left: 40px;&quot;&gt;Â· 2-4 years Sr. HR Generalist Experience&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p style=&quot;padding-left: 40px;&quot;&gt;Â· Understanding of employment law&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p style=&quot;padding-left: 40px;&quot;&gt;Â· Excellent Collaborator&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p style=&quot;padding-left: 40px;&quot;&gt;Â· Strong skills using Microsoft Office Suite&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p style=&quot;padding-left: 40px;&quot;&gt;Â· Willingness to take initiative&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p style=&quot;padding-left: 40px;&quot;&gt;Â· Strong communication skills, both oral and written&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p style=&quot;padding-left: 40px;&quot;&gt;Â· Bachelorâ€™s degree in human resources or related field preferred&lt;/p&gt;', '2020-08-06 01:53:41'),
(52, '2225522', '6sense', 'Senior IT Admin', 'Tech', 'Pune, Maharashtra', 'http://platform_1.com/jobs/2225522', 'http://public-logo.com/6sense', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;IT Support Specialist&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Description:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;6sense is looking for a motived IT Support Specialist to join our team. As 6senseâ€™s first dedicated member of IT, you will have the opportunity to be an instrumental figure in the development of our IT department and will help to set the standard for how we take care of our internal stakeholders.&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate will streamline our processes and maintain the integrity of all employeesâ€™ computer workstations and associated software. The IT Support Specialistwill also be the primary point of contact for computer, video conferencing, and network issues had by 6senseâ€™s internal stakeholders.&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;This is a great opportunity to join a growing company and help us reach our IT goals. This role is remote but may require periodical travel to support our growing team of over 100 US employees across15 states, with 5 offices.&lt;br&gt; &lt;br&gt; &lt;strong&gt;The Company:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;6sense helps B2B marketing and sales organizations fully understand the complex ABM buyer journey. By combining intent signals from every channel with the industryâ€™s most advanced AI predictive capabilities, it is finally possible to predict account demand and optimize demand generation in an ABM world. Equipped with the power of AI and the 6sense Demand Platformâ„¢, marketing and sales professionals can uncover, accelerate, and capture buyer demand to drive more revenue.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;ul&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Provide exceptional IT support to internal users, across geographical locations ensuring an overall high level of satisfaction of an ongoing basis&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Order and configure new laptops, to ensure all new hires are prepared for their employment at 6sense&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Create and maintain inventory tracking system for IT equipment&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Spearhead new projects to update and improve IT within the company&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Troubleshoot hardware and software issues in person, remotely and via phone&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;ul&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Bachelorâ€™s degree preferred&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;4+ years of experience working in corporate IT environments&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Proven track record of maintaining IT structural integrity&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Understanding of IT principles and an ability to communicate technical concepts effectively to a varied audience&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Excellent written and verbal communication skills&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Flexible schedule allowing for support of after-hours, in-house events, and travel to other offices&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Microsoft Office 365 administrative experience&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Mac and PC experience&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Single sign-on experience&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nice-to-have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;ul&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated success with assessing and implementing various levels of IT/AV needed for the different types of rooms across spaces&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Proven experience working in a fast-growing tech company, with remote employees&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Self-motivated, goal-oriented and problem solver with an action-oriented approach&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;', '2020-07-29 12:18:51'),
(53, '2160416', '6sense', 'Senior Product Manager', 'Product', 'San Francisco, CA', 'http://platform_1.com/jobs/2160416', 'http://public-logo.com/6sense', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Description:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;Imagine being responsible for driving a product from paper concept to â€˜in the customerâ€™s handâ€™ reality. Imagine enabling a growing start-up company and product team to drive business transformation at companies like GE, Salesforce, ADP, Dell and others with impact to a customer&#39;s top line. And imagine doing all that without the big company bureaucracy that slows down experimentation and progress of a product team.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;As a Senior Manager of Product Management at 6sense, you&#39;ll be an instrumental player to help us grow the emerging market of predictive intelligence for sales and marketing. We have a superior technology position and growing customer base, and you will be a key contributor to help us accelerate growth through identifying and delivering upon unique product value propositions. You will drive some of our core products designed to meet the customer and market need while maintaining the overall company strategy.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;This position reports to the VP of Product, and we&#39;re looking for someone that has a strong technical and analytical background, exceptional at executing a product roadmap, can get into the mind of our target customer, and can iterate with customers, customer success, user experience, and the executive team to build compelling customer value. You need to be an integrative thinker with high attention-to-detail, a strong communicator, a great problem-solver, and a hard worker.&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;The Company:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;The 6sense Account Based Orchestration Platform helps revenue teams identify and close more opportunities by putting the power of AI, big data and machine learning behind every member of the B2B revenue team, empowering them to uncover anonymous buying behavior, prioritize fragmented data to focus on accounts in market, and engage resistant buying teams with personalized, multi-channel, multi-touch campaigns. 6sense helps revenue teams know everything they need to know about their buyers so they can easily do anything they need to do to generate more opportunities, increase deal size, get into opportunities sooner, compete and win more often.&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;ul&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Be a customer advocate and organizational glue, championing customer needs via customer discovery sessions and understanding industry trends that will drive our product vision&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Gather requirements from users, customers, sales, support and internal stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Develop use cases and product requirements to communicate these needs to engineering and user experience&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Work with the product management team to coordinate and drive roadmap, positioning, requirements, and track feature delivery&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Work with sales and customer success teams to drive process and product improvements&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Support product marketing to create customer driven messaging and content&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum Required Skills&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;ul&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated ability to build, own, communicate, and drive the roadmap of at least one product through cross-functional collaboration and research&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated ability to manage and prioritize multiple projects for different stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated ability to communicate complex feature requirements, capture clear user stories, and design appropriate product feature metrics&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated ability to understand technical challenges with software-as-a-service offerings, and work hands-on with engineering and user experience teams to find solutions&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated ability to provide product demonstrations&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Superior verbal communication and presentation skills in translating product concepts and issues into implications and actions&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Experience in a fast-paced Agile and Web Development environment&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Excellent interpersonal skills and ability to connect with customers and partners&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Native-level English written and spoken skill is required&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum Required Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;ul&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Background or product management experience in marketing tech, sales tech, or ad tech space&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Academic background in computer science or related engineering discipline that will enable you to easily communicate with the engineering team; MBA preferred&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;4+ years of product management experience working with enterprise customers; ideally managing at least one product through an entire development cycle from concept to launch&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;', '2020-07-29 12:18:51'),
(54, '2274743', '6sense', 'Senior Recruiter', 'G&A', 'Unites States', 'http://platform_1.com/jobs/2274743', 'http://public-logo.com/6sense', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THE COMPANY:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;The 6sense Account Based Orchestration Platform helps revenue teams identify and close more opportunities by putting the power of AI, big data and machine learning behind every member of the B2B revenue team, empowering them to uncover anonymous buying behavior, prioritize fragmented data to focus on accounts in market, and engage resistant buying teams with personalized, multi-channel, multi-touch campaigns. 6sense helps revenue teams know everything they need to know about their buyers so they can easily do anything they need to do to generate more opportunities, increase deal size, get into opportunities sooner, compete and win more often.&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THE ROLE:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Primary responsibility is overseeing the full life-cycle recruiting and employee retention process that includes but not limited to recruiting, screening and recommending candidates using creative sourcing methods (internal and external), contributing to the organization&#39;s DE&amp;amp;I managing prospect relations, on-boarding new employees, marketing 6sense brand in growth stage startup circles, employee engagement, and retention etc.&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;RESPONSIBILITIES:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;ul&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Oversees the full life cycle of the recruiting process by screening resumes, interviewing candidates (by phone and in person), administers appropriate assessments when required, conducts reference/background checking; works with hiring manager on making recommendations for hire (or not hire) and delivers employment offers for both exempt and nonexempt position openings.&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Uses the applicant tracking module in Greenhouse to manage the recruiting process.&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Uses traditional and nontraditional resources, such as career fairs, online job fairs, community network events, etc., to identify and attract quality candidates.&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Develops advertising programs (internal and external) to ensure high visibility with potential candidates in the local community and throughout the area.&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Communicates important employment information during delivery of employment offers (e.g., benefits, compensation).&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Works with hiring managers to ensure compliance with all regulations.&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Conduct on-boarding and off-boarding of employees.&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;HR related administrative tasks.&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Conceive and drive employee engagement programs.&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Culture building.&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Other duties as assigned.&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;JOB REQUIREMENTS&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;ul&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;At least 2 years of hands on experience involved in the full life-cycle recruiting.&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Hands on HRIS experience strongly preferred.&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;A can do attitude and commitment to providing excellent customer service to employees, candidates, business partners, and clients.&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Ability to work autonomously and use resources available to complete tasks timely.&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Experience managing change in a rapidly changing and a growing, culturally diverse environment.&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;A demonstrated track record of managing and prioritizing multiple projects while meeting deadlines.&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Excellent written and verbal communication and presentation skills.&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Strong professional presence, ability to interact with various internal and external stakeholders and gain respect quickly.&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Demonstrate ability to appropriately handle confidential information and sensitive situations in a reliable manner.&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;', '2020-07-31 13:30:40');
