(55, '1261053', '6sense', 'Senior Software Engineer - Infrastructure', 'Tech', 'San Francisco', 'http://platform_1.com/jobs/1261053', 'http://public-logo.com/6sense', '&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Company&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;6sense helps B2B marketing and sales organizations fully understand the complex ABM buyer journey. By combining intent signals from every channel with the industryâ€™s most advanced AI predictive capabilities, it is finally possible to predict account demand and optimize demand generation in an ABM world. Equipped with the power of AI and the 6sense Demand Platformâ„¢, marketing and sales professionals can uncover, accelerate, and capture buyer demand to drive more revenue.&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;h3&gt;The Role&lt;/h3&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;Infrastructure Software Engineers at 6sense are true hybrid developers and operations&amp;nbsp;engineers. They are responsible for ensuring our services and infrastructure are fast, stable, and scalable. They build out any services and tooling we need that are not readily available via third-party packages or services. They provide guidance on best practices to the overall Software Engineering team.&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;Operational tasks such as infrastructure, build/release, CI/CD, database administration, and systems administration also fall within their realm of responsibilities.&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;\n&lt;ul class=&quot;uiList _53x5 _53xc _4of _4kg&quot;&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Develop and deploy services&amp;nbsp;to improve the availability, ease of use/management, and visibility of 6sense systems&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Architecting, building, and scaling out our services and infrastructure&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Learning and adopting technologies that may aide in solving our challenges&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li class=&quot;_3-8x _3-95&quot;&gt;\n&lt;div class=&quot;fcb&quot;&gt;Own our systems like our Hadoop and Presto clusters, front/back-end services,&amp;nbsp;build configurations,&amp;nbsp;infrastructure components, deployment of services into our infrastructure, and everything in between&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li class=&quot;_3-8x _3-95&quot;&gt;\n&lt;div class=&quot;fcb&quot;&gt;Write/review/debug production code, develop documentation and capacity plans, and debug live production problems&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li class=&quot;_3-8x _3-95&quot;&gt;\n&lt;div class=&quot;fcb&quot;&gt;Contributing back to open-source projects if we need to add or patch functionality&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Support the overall Software Engineering team to resolve any issues they encounter&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;\n&lt;ul&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;1+ years of experience with Linux/Unix system administration and networking fundamentals&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;2+ years in a Software Engineering role or equivalent experience&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Strong skills in reading code as well as writing clean, maintainable, and scalable code&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Good knowledge of Python and Java&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Experience designing, building, and maintaining scalable services and/or service-oriented architecture&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Experience with high-availability&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bonus Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;\n&lt;ul&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Experience with modern configuration management tools (e.g. Ansible, Chef, Puppet) and idempotency&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Exposure to modern build systems&amp;nbsp;such as Bazel, Buck, or Pants&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of the Hadoop ecosystem (e.g. Hadoop, Hive, Presto) including deployment, scaling, and maintenance&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of standard security practices&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;1+ years of experience working with Kubernetes, Docker&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Good knowledge of Javascript&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;#LI-PS1&lt;/p&gt;', '2020-08-06 03:31:46'),
(56, '2054358', '6sense', 'Senior Solutions Consultant', 'Customer Success', 'Central Region', 'http://platform_1.com/jobs/2054358', 'http://public-logo.com/6sense', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;Imagine selling a solution that will predict for your customers (with an 85% accuracy) who is going to buy, what theyâ€™ll buy and when.&amp;nbsp; As a Solutions Consultant at 6sense, youâ€™ll be an instrumental player to our growth as we build upon the success weâ€™ve had delivering predictions for enterprises like Cisco, CSC, Lenovo, BlueJeans and Xactly.&amp;nbsp; We will trust you to evangelize 6sense with a focus on both pre and post sales efforts.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Company:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;6sense helps B2B marketing and sales organizations fully understand the complex ABM buyer journey. By combining intent signals from every channel with the industryâ€™s most advanced AI predictive capabilities, it is finally possible to predict account demand and optimize demand generation in an ABM world. Equipped with the power of AI and the 6sense Demand Platformâ„¢, marketing and sales professionals can uncover, accelerate, and capture buyer demand to drive more revenue.&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Fit:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;Weâ€™re in the early stages of building our solutions consulting team so weâ€™re looking for people who not only have a track record of being the best of the best, but can also think critically about driving customer growth and building our SC organization.&amp;nbsp; This is a unique opportunity to help shape and accelerate our success.&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;Here are the traits you exhibit;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;ul&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Intrinsic drive to be successful, love to win â€“ Youâ€™ll take initiative to figure it out, are motivated to do your absolute best work. (Thatâ€™s why youâ€™ve ended up at top across your career.)&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Clear, succinct communicator â€“ Using your customerâ€™s language, youâ€™ll help them clearly understand the value 6sense delivers&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Technical expertise â€“ Youâ€™ll demonstrate and speak to&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;how&lt;/em&gt;&amp;nbsp;6sense drives success&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Innately curious â€“ Youâ€™ll know your buyer, their business, and what 6sense means to their success&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Empathetic listener â€“ Youâ€™ll listen more than you talk. And, you really get what they mean.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Collaborate and win as a team â€“ Youâ€™ll compete, but above that youâ€™ll collaborate, youâ€™ll share what is working, youâ€™ll help the team win, youâ€™ll take on projects outside of closing deals.&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;We are creating a different kind of company. If this sounds like a breath of fresh air and a place where youâ€™ll thrive as you take your success to the next level, we should talk!&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;ul&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;2+ years in a sales engineer, solutions consulting role&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Strong knowledge of marketing tech ecosystem, including web analytics, content management, marketing automation, and CRM&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Deep understanding of enterprise sales cycles and engagement&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Ability to articulate the technical and functional capabilities of 6sense to both marketing and sales audiences&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Ability to manage RFI/RFPs with tight deadlines&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Experience working directly with product and engineering&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Experience building content, documentation&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Willingness to travel up to 25%&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Strong presentation skills&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;ul&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Experience selling to Enterprise CMOs, VPs Demand Gen, Marketing Operations, Sales leaders&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Strong and demonstrated written and verbal communications skills&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Ability to work in a fast-paced, team environment&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;4-year BA/BS degree or equivalent practical experience&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;', '2020-07-29 12:18:51'),
(57, '2011413', '6sense', 'Senior Strategic Advisor', 'Customer Success', 'Austin, Texas, United States, Remote', 'http://platform_1.com/jobs/2011413', 'http://public-logo.com/6sense', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Senior Strategic Advisor&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Target Location: SF or Austin, Remote Acceptable.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Company &amp;amp; Team:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;Thereâ€™s an explosion of data as B2B buyers shift their buying to the web, but making sense of this data alone is no small feat. The data-driven sales and marketing organizations that align around the tools to leverage this data will gain competitive dominance in their markets.&amp;nbsp; At the forefront of the hottest space (predictive intelligence) within the fastest growing tech segment (marketing tech), lies 6sense.&amp;nbsp; At 6sense, our mission is to provide leading companies with 100% visibility into buyers -- clearing the way for marketing and sales professionals to reach new heights of efficiency and success.&amp;nbsp; We are solving a hard problem that delivers unquestionable, game-changing ROI (read; big deals).&amp;nbsp; Forrester just rated 6sense as the leader #1 vendor in Predictive Marketing Analytics. Having raised $36M (backed by&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.linkedin.com/pulse/rise-intent-based-b2b-marketing-indranil-indy-guha&quot;&gt;Bain Venture Capital&lt;/a&gt;, &amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.strictlyvc.com/2014/05/19/battery-ventures-venrock-back-6sense-12-million/&quot;&gt;Battery Ventures&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;and &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.venrock.com/&quot;&gt;Venrock&lt;/a&gt;), we are rapidly growing the customer success team in San Francisco.&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;The Strategic Advisory team is the customer success SWAT team, we support 6senseâ€™s most complex and critical customers with hands-on advisory services through a paid professional services model. We are experienced GTM professionals with a clear vision for how ABM can help organizations realize major business returns at scale and itâ€™s our job to help customers achieve this vision.&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;The Strategic Advisor acts as a trusted strategic advisor in client engagements, working with our customerâ€™s GTM leadership and executional teams to develop the plans, processes and best practices that will deliver results.&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;The role may support a wide range of strategic needs including:&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;ul&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Guiding an organizationâ€™s ABM transition strategy&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Advising clients on the creation of an ABM campaign approach&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Assessing organizational maturity to identify key use cases for 6sense adoption&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Supporting the design &amp;amp; implementation of new GTM programs and processes,&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Assessing program performance and providing recommendations for improvement&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;Weâ€™re looking for someone who will be viewed as a thought leader, a trusted expert and GTM peer for our customers. We are focused on candidates that can share their deep understanding of the B2B revenue world and express a desire to source, manage and own a book of business focused on helping 6sense customers develop cutting-edge ABM strategies with our platform. The ideal candidate will also be a team player capable of supporting our organization beyond just client engagements, someone willing to help our sales team close major deals or guide our customer success teams through unique challenges they face with customers - this personâ€™s expertise will be valuable across all of 6senseâ€™s operations.&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;br&gt; &lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Requirements:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;ul&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;4 year degree from a highly rated program&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;3-7 years in a B2B Demand Marketing Leadership or Campaigns / ABM-aligned Role&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Desired Skills &amp;amp; Characteristics:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;ul&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strong Program Management Skills&lt;/strong&gt; â€“ Youâ€™re on top of your work, know how to plan out and manage an execution timeline, and keep meticulous notes.&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Autonomous &amp;amp; Collaborative&lt;/strong&gt; â€“ Able work independently and own your own projects and results, while also able to work alongside other functions as a team focused on delivering the best customer experience&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategic Problem Solver&lt;/strong&gt; â€“ Comfortable with ambiguous situations, driven to find solutions and answers quickly, and able to translate long-term strategies into action to deliver value&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Customer Oriented&lt;/strong&gt; â€“ You are comfortable developing, managing and growing relationships with all customers â€“ not just clients &amp;amp; prospects, but internal stakeholders as well. You will be viewed as a trusted expert that can be relied on in many situations to provide advice and guidance.&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Analytical &amp;amp; Systems Minded&lt;/strong&gt; â€“ You can quickly interpret and create a narrative from data. Process challenges are visible to you through analysis and you can guide the development of analytical approaches across systems to deliver performance and operational insights.&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Desired Knowledge &amp;amp; Experience:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;ul&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Experience working across multi-channel B2B programs &amp;amp; campaigns with exposure to\n&lt;ul&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Media planning &amp;amp; Execution&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Campaign &amp;amp; Audience planning&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Messaging Planning &amp;amp; Execution&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Demand campaign &amp;amp; media analytics&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with ABM concepts and program design including\n&lt;ul&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Account-based Audience Design&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;ABM platforms and technologies&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;ABM media execution&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;ABM sales enablement &amp;amp; research&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Exposure to &amp;amp; familiarity with Sales Enablement and Outbound Sales Functions including\n&lt;ul&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Outbound play design &amp;amp; sales enablement&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Sales prospecting &amp;amp; lead follow-up process&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Outreach sequence development&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Understanding of marketing &amp;amp; sales operations and technology including\n&lt;ul&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;MarTech systems, capabilities and data integrations&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Marketing lead management process &amp;amp; scoring approaches&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Sales opportunity cycle management &amp;amp; measurement&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Bonus Points for:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;ul&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Prior consulting / professional-services experience&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Customer-facing marketing or agency experience&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;MBA or Masters in Marketing&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;', '2020-07-29 12:18:51'),
(58, '2252729', '6sense', 'Software Development Engineer in Test - SDET', 'Tech', 'Pune', 'http://platform_1.com/jobs/2252729', 'http://public-logo.com/6sense', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Title: SDET Engineer&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;6sense is a Predictive Intelligence Engine that is reimagining how B2B companies do sales and marketing. It works with big data at scale, advanced machine learning and predictive modelling to find buyers and predict what they will purchase, when and how much.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;6sense helps B2B marketing and sales organizations fully understand the complex ABM buyer journey. By combining intent signals from every channel with the industryâ€™s most advanced AI predictive capabilities, it is finally possible to predict account demand and optimize demand generation in an ABM world. Equipped with the power of AI and the 6sense Demand Platformâ„¢, marketing and sales professionals can uncover, accelerate, and capture buyer demand to drive more revenue.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;6sense is seeking a SDET Engineer for our Pune office to work within our tech team and develop test strategy, collaborate with different teams.&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A&amp;nbsp;SDET Engineer&amp;nbsp;at 6Sense will have the opportunity to:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;br&gt; &lt;br&gt; - Plan, monitor and control all testing activities and tasks across respective Releases &amp;amp; projects.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt; - Responsible for analysis, design, development and execution of test cases and test suites.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt; - Responsible for the work product of the testing across projects and the timely delivery of different testing milestones&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt; - Monitor the scheduling and readiness of test environments (including interfaces and data setup) for each test stage&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt; - Collaborate with development team and onshore team for application test activities&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt; - Responsible for automating manual test cases for reducing manual effort.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt; - Sharing test results to senior management on daily basis, update the status in Jira and test management tool.&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Desired Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;- Education- BE/B.Tech in Computer Science or equivalent (IT, electronics) from one of the premier institutes in India.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;- Minimum 8 years of experience in Software testing (Manual, functional, regression, sanity etc.)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;- Minimum 2+ year of experience in Automation testing using Selenium, Protractor or Cypress.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;- Must have a deep understanding of Software testing life cycle, Software testing methodologies and QA procedures&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;- Must understand the uses and methods of testing&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;- Must have strong knowledge in testing skills (design test plan and test strategy, writing test cases, executing test cases, opening bugs, verifying bugs)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;- Minimum 2+ years of experience with API testing&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;- Minimum 2+ years of experience of working in an agile, fast-paced environment&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;- Minimum 2+ years of experience in test management and defect management tools e.g. ALM, JIRA, BugZilla etc.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;- Good level in SQL/database&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Interpersonal Attributes:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;- Critical thinker and problem-solving skills; team player&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;- Excellent organizational skills, having the ability to prioritize workload whilst being resilient and being able to cope well under pressure and meeting tight deadlines&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;- Excellent communication skills, both written and verbal&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;- Comfortable with change and learning new things, working outside of comfort zone&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;- Work on multiple projects concurrently and be able to prioritize tasks and set expectations.&lt;/p&gt;', '2020-07-29 12:18:51'),
