(73, '4782018002', '98point6', 'Senior Front End Software Engineer', 'Front End Engineering', 'Seattle HQ', 'http://platform_1.com/jobs/4782018002', 'http://public-logo.com/98point6', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Our mission is to deliver high-quality primary care that is accessible, convenient and affordable for all. Every single day youâ€™ll be working on challenging problems with an exceptional team to profoundly transform primary care and improve peopleâ€™s quality of life.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Role and Impact&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;In this role, you will build web applications using a modern TypeScript stack based on React and Redux. You will work with a team of engineers focused on rapid feature development, correctness, stability and continual improvement. You will be at the forefront of software design, bridging service engineering and front-end development.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;ul&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Working on a small feature team that builds and supports web apps for our clinic&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Contribute to and help influence the direction of our web app architecture by working across teams to ensure weâ€™re building the right things the right way&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Collaborate with our product and design team members throughout our development life cycle, from ideation to execution&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Active participation in code and design reviews to ensure weâ€™re meeting product and platform quality standards&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Provide mentorship across the engineering organization&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;ul&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;8+ years of software development experience&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Experience supporting a feature through the full life cycleâ€”from gathering requirements all the way to production&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Experience in Javascript, HTML5, CSS3 and at least one modern Javascript framework like React, Vue or Angular&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Successful experience working with and mentoring junior engineers&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Experience with writing unit and integration tests&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;ul&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Experience with ES6 and functional programming&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Experience with CI/CD pipelines and automation services, such as Jenkins&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Experience with AWS services, such as Lambda and DynamoDB&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;98point6 provides equal employment opportunities to all without regard to race, color, religion, sex (including sexual orientation or gender identity), national origin, age, disability, genetic information or other protected status.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', '2020-07-29 13:30:31'),
(74, '4206866002', '98point6', 'Senior Product Security Engineer', 'Security Engineering', 'Seattle HQ', 'http://platform_1.com/jobs/4206866002', 'http://public-logo.com/98point6', '&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Our mission is to deliver high-quality primary care that is accessible, convenient and affordable for all. Every single day youâ€™ll be working on challenging problems with an exceptional team to profoundly transform primary care and improve peopleâ€™s quality of life.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Role and Impact&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;As a product security engineer at 98point6, you will collaborate with internal teams that deal with PHI belonging to a large number of patients and it is imperative that this data is secured. We are building our security team to help safeguard this information, and your work will improve our overall security posture. From testing an application to reviewing the overall network architecture, conducting trainings for our engineering team to writing our own tools to automate a workflow, you will be empowered to do the work that is most important for the organization. You will demonstrate the 98point6 core values daily as part of a unique culture driven to achieve our audacious goals.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div&gt;\n&lt;ul&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Conduct code reviews of our applications and security configuration reviews of our AWS infrastructure&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Design, implement, execute and report on penetration tests of our services and infrastructure&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Contribute a security perspective to our application and infrastructure design process&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Develop threat models for our current and planned systems and infrastructure&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Conduct or organize security training and outreach for our development teams&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Design and develop security tools to improve our automated monitoring&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Identify key performance metrics for security metrics and implement instrumentation for those metrics&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Develop and execute our processes for security event incident response&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Perform third-party vendor security assessments and verify security compliance of vendors over time&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div&gt;\n&lt;ul&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;6+ years of experience in the security industry working in any combination of the following areas: threat modeling, secure coding, web and mobile application security, identity management and authentication, software development, cloud security or penetration testing&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Experience implementing security solutions in mobile apps, web apps and backend services&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Experience writing and reviewing code (Java, Python, Node or similar)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Experience working effectively with software engineering teams&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Excellent written and verbal communication skills&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Experience responding to security events preferred&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;98point6 provides equal employment opportunities to all without regard to race, color, religion, sex (including sexual orientation or gender identity), national origin, age, disability, genetic information or other protected status.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', '2020-07-29 13:30:25'),
(75, '1484846', '', 'Deep Learning Engineer', 'Wayfinder', 'Sunnyvale, CA', 'http://platform_1.com/jobs/1484846', 'http://public-logo.com/a', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Wayfinder&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Project Wayfinder is building scalable, certifiable autonomy systems to power self-piloted aircraft applications throughout Airbus, from small urban air vehicles (aka air taxis) to large commercial airplanes. Our team of experts is driving the maturation of machine learning and other core technologies for autonomous flight; we are creating a reference architecture that includes hardware, software, and a data-driven development process to allow aircraft to perceive and react to their environment. Autonomous flight is transforming the transportation industry - our team is at the heart of this revolution.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Opportunity&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;As a Deep Learning Engineer, you will report directly to the Director of Engineering of Wayfinder. You will be responsible for the development of vision-based deep learning algorithms that enable autonomous aircraft to analyze, understand, and interact with their environment safely. These perception algorithms are critical to enabling our aircraft to fly without pilots.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;ul&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Designing, training, and tuning state-of-the-art vision-based deep learning algorithms to perceive the environment around autonomous aircraft on the ground and in the air;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Driving the efficient implementation of these algorithms for deployment to onboard computer systems;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Supporting the data flows that enable the development and testing of deep learning algorithms;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Communicating methods and results effectively to the rest of our team.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;ul&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;We expect you to have a masterâ€™s degree in computer science, robotics, electrical engineering, applied mathematics, computational neuroscience, or a related field and at least two years of professional experience related to computer vision applications. We also expect you will have:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Strong knowledge of neural network architectures and computer vision algorithms for scene understanding including object detection, classification, segmentation, depth and motion estimation;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Experience developing novel deep learning models with TensorFlow, PyTorch, Caffe, or another common framework;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Expertise in Python, Java, or C++;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Demonstrated ability to maintain currency with the latest developments in your field;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Personal drive and intellectual curiosity to do what hasnâ€™t been done before, coupled with an appreciation for overcoming challenges.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strongly preferred qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;ul&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Real-world experience with mobile autonomous systems such as robots, cars, and UAVs;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Familiarity with sensors including cameras, radar, and lidar;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Expertise in developing for GPU computation;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Experience optimizing trained deep learning models for deployment;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Software development experience in a production environment.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;ul&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Daily lunch and snacks, happy hours; social outings&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Exceptional PPO medical, dental and vision benefits 100% covered for employee and their family/dependents&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Generous PTO of 5 weeks (25 days) in addition to 10 national holidays&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Tuition reimbursement for professional development or $15,750 for flight training&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;3 months paid parental leave from Day 1&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;Employee discounts through Airbus Tickets @Work, gym subsidy and more&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;', '2020-07-29 14:07:28'),
