(164, '2190936', 'Earnin', 'Sr. Mobile Engineer, Android', 'Engineering', 'Vancouver, Palo Alto', 'http://platform_1.com/jobs/2190936', 'http://public-logo.com/activehours', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sr. Mobile Engineer, Android&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Earnin:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Earnin is a community-supported financial platform with a suite of tools that let people take control of their financial future. Earnin started out by solving one of the greatest â€“ and least discussed â€“ inequities in the American financial system: the practice of employers paying workers bi-weekly. Earnin&#39;s core product, Cash Out, allows people to access the pay they&#39;ve already earned. There are no loans or hidden costs. People pay what they choose. Other products include: Balance Shield, which helps prevent overdrafts, a financial calendar that helps people budget and schedule payments, and Tip Yourself - a revolutionary free social savings app.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Funding: Series C, current funding partners include Andreessen Horowitz, DST, Matrix Partners, Ribbit Capital, Felicis Ventures and March Capital.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Join us and help build a new financial system focused on fairness and peopleâ€™s needs.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;You can help make a difference.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Team:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Since Earnin is a mobile-only application, the mobile engineering teamâ€™s job is to develop new features and support our best in class iOS and Android applications.&amp;nbsp; We work closely with the product, marketing, server engineering, and customer support teams to create new product experiences for our customers.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Our goal is to provide our customers with a solid mobile experience that helps them gain access to their money easily and understand quickly any problems or issues that may arise on their account.&amp;nbsp; Engineers joining the mobile team must have a solid focus on user experience as well as understand mobile-specific issues ranging from network usage to battery life.&amp;nbsp; The mobile engineering team is the most customer-facing group and has a big impact on the customerâ€™s impression of our company.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What Set Us Apart:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;ul&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;We care more about the thought process, perseverance, tenacity in solving really difficult problems (rather than checking off all the technology boxes).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Solving unique problems in the financial payments industry&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;As a Mobile Engineer you will:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;ul&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Work with the product and design team on creating new user experiences and features.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Design and implement new APIs with our server engineering team to communicate with the mobile applications.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Create and monitor analytics to prove how effective new and existing features are to helping customers.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Some skills we consider critical to being a Mobile Android Engineer:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;ul&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;5+ years developing and shipping Android applications.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Fluency in Java and Kotlin / specifically on the Android platform.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Experience writing flexible layouts for different screen sizes/densities.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Proficient with Android Studio.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;5+ years of experience with mobile-specific considerations like CPU and memory performance, network usage, and battery consumption.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;5+ years of experience with client/server architectures using HTTP/HTTPS, JSON, REST.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Bachelor&#39;s, Masterâ€™s or PhD degree in computer science, computer engineering or a related technical discipline or equivalent industry experience.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Computer Science background with an understanding of data structures and algorithms.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Excellent written and verbal communication skills.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Ability to thrive in a fast-paced, dynamic environment and you have a bias towards action and results&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Earnin does not unlawfully discriminate on the basis of race, color, religion, sex (including pregnancy, childbirth, breastfeeding or related medical conditions), gender identity, gender expression, national origin, ancestry, citizenship, age, physical or mental disability, legally&amp;nbsp;protected medical condition, family care status, military or veteran status, marital status, registered domestic partner status, sexual orientation, genetic information, or any other basis protected by local, state, or federal laws. Earnin is an E-Verify participant.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Earnin does not accept unsolicited resumes from individual recruiters or third party recruiting agencies in response to job postings. No fee will be paid to third parties who submit unsolicited candidates directly to our hiring managers or HR team.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;', '2020-07-29 15:48:20'),
(165, '2253297', 'Earnin', 'Sr. Site Reliability Engineer', 'Engineering', 'Palo Alto, CA', 'http://platform_1.com/jobs/2253297', 'http://public-logo.com/activehours', '&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sr. Site Reliability Engineer&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;\n&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Earnin:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Earnin is a community-supported financial platform with a suite of tools that let people take control of their financial future. Earnin started out by solving one of the greatest â€“ and least discussed â€“ inequities in the American financial system: the practice of employers paying workers bi-weekly. Earnin&#39;s core product, Cash Out, allows people to access the pay they&#39;ve already earned. There are no loans or hidden costs. People pay what they choose. Other products include: Balance Shield, which helps prevent overdrafts, a financial calendar that helps people budget and schedule payments, and Tip Yourself - a revolutionary free social savings app.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Funding: Series C, current funding partners include Andreessen Horowitz, DST, Matrix Partners, Ribbit Capital, Felicis Ventures and March Capital.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Join us and help build a new financial system focused on fairness and peopleâ€™s needs.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;You can help make a difference.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About The Team:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;We have a real passion for delivering the best product experience for our community members. We work closely with all teams and share the responsibility to rapidly deliver production-ready features to our community. At the core we use Service Level Objectives (SLOs) using Key Performance Indicators (KPIs) to build accountability for all. We build or contribute to infrastructure and software solutions to accomplish this.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About The Role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;As a Senior, SRE youâ€™ll be the subject matter expert with operating systems and networking. Youâ€™ll understand how our services are performing, we use DataDog (Logging+Metrics+APM), Prometheus, and Cloudwatch (by way of Datadog) to alert with Slack or PagerDuty. We are strong believers in Infrastructure as Code. There are many ways to accomplish this, but we use Terraform, Ansible, and Kubernetes to make it happen. Our .NET Core/Framework and Python applications run on AWS. We leverage a mixture of EC2, ASG and EKS for compute, ELB and AppMesh for load balancing and proxy, Kineses, SQS, Kafka for streaming data, and DynamoDB, RDS, ElastiCache for state storage.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About You:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h3&gt;\n&lt;ul&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;You have a software background and are passionate about optimizing quality of service and developer experience&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Youâ€™re calm and collected, cool under pressure, and not afraid to voice your&amp;nbsp; opinion (even in the heat of an incident).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Youâ€™re excited to work with both technical and non-technical teams throughout our organization&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;You have proven experience working with large-scale, secure, and performant distributed systems&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;You enjoy sharing information to reduce silos and break down barriers between teams&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Youâ€™re passionate about learning new technologies and adopting the right tools to manage these services in production -- keeping SLAs and MTTR in mind at all times.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;You have the ability to plan, lead, and execute on strategic objectives for the team or all of engineering.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Youâ€™re familiar with all of the PagerDuty ringtones available&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You have:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h3&gt;\n&lt;ul&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Masters or bachelors degree in computer science, or 5+ years of experience in an SRE or Software Engineering role&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Successfully managed production environments at scale and understand that you need more than a for-loop and ssh to make it happen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;You know that observability is critically important to run highly available and performant services.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;ul&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;SLO, SLI, and KPI are more than TLAs to you&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Youâ€™ve read (or written) part of or all of the SRE book and have contextualized it for different engineering teams and cultures.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Hands-on experience with shepherding services from design to production.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Youâ€™ve tackled site-wide outages, lessons were learned, and you know how to make sure that&amp;nbsp; it never happens again.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Youâ€™re passionate about mentoring junior engineers and you believe in the investment of people.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;At Earnin, we believe that the best way to build a financial system that works for everyday people is by hiring a team that represents our diverse community. Our team is diverse not only in background and experience, but also in perspective. We celebrate our diversity and strive to create a culture of belonging. Earnin does not unlawfully discriminate on the basis of race, color, religion, sex (including pregnancy, childbirth, breastfeeding or related medical conditions), gender identity, gender expression, national origin, ancestry, citizenship, age, physical or mental disability, legally protected medical condition, family care status, military or veteran status, marital status, registered domestic partner status, sexual orientation, genetic information, or any other basis protected by local, state, or federal laws. Earnin is an E-Verify participant.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Earnin does not accept unsolicited resumes from individual recruiters or third party recruiting agencies in response to job postings. No fee will be paid to third parties who submit unsolicited candidates directly to our hiring managers or HR team.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', '2020-07-29 15:48:20'),
(166, '2158384', 'Earnin', 'Treasury Lead', 'Finance', 'Palo Alto, CA', 'http://platform_1.com/jobs/2158384', 'http://public-logo.com/activehours', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Earnin:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;Earnin is a community-supported financial platform with a suite of tools that let people take control of their financial future. Earnin started out by solving one of the greatest â€“ and least discussed â€“ inequities in the American financial system: the practice of employers paying workers bi-weekly. Earnin&#39;s core product, Cash Out, allows people to access the pay they&#39;ve already earned. There are no loans or hidden costs. People pay what they choose. Other products include: Balance Shield, which helps prevent overdrafts, a financial calendar that helps people budget and schedule payments, and Tip Yourself - a revolutionary free social savings app.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;Funding: Series C, current funding partners include Andreessen Horowitz, DST, Matrix Partners, Ribbit Capital, Felicis Ventures and March Capital.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;Join us and help build a new financial system focused on fairness and peopleâ€™s needs.&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;You can help make a difference.&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Team:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;We are seeking a Treasury Lead to build, own and manage the function. Join the small, but growing Finance team, working closely with the CFO to deliver on key initiatives for the company in 2020. Earninâ€™s unique business model and product offer interesting opportunities for the treasury function to have outsized impact on company-wide initiatives. Areas of ownership include: cash management and forecasting; debt facility operations; managing external banking &amp;amp; lending relationships; internal expert on Earninâ€™s debt facilities for cross-functional workflows; shareholder reporting and equity management; and debt capital market functions.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;As Treasury Lead you will:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;ul&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Manage the treasury function, including meeting short-term and long-term funding needs&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Develop cash and debt management strategies and processes with the goals of minimizing Earninâ€™s working capital need and reducing our net interest expense&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Manage Earninâ€™s debt facilities, including the production of borrowing bases and required reporting. Automating and optimizing this critical process is a priority&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Recommend and establish a multi-year roadmap for the companyâ€™s debt financing needs&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Contribute to capital market functions, including identifying new debt partners or structures, maintaining existing relationships, and managing capital raises&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Recommend financing structures that optimize the companyâ€™s cost, stability, and flexibility of capital&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Work cross-functionally with product, engineer, and internal business partners in the development and optimization of products to ensure the funding and cash flow components are well understood.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Monitor and ensure compliance with debt covenants and all other other compliance requirements related to debt or cash management&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Manage banking and lender relationships to satisfy reporting requirements, communicate changes to the business, and drive improvements in operational processes&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Own corporate equity administration, including shareholder reporting responsibilities and secondary sales of company equity&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Serve as companyâ€™s representative to financial community and shareholders&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Participate in the development of annual operating and business fiscal plans (budgets)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Other treasury functions may be in scope as the candidate grows the function along with the needs of the business, including tax, corporate risk management, and A/R &amp;amp; A/P vendor management&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What youâ€™ll bring:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;ul&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Bachelorâ€™s degree in accounting, business, management, or finance preferred&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Strong treasury background (7+ years of experience in finance and treasury)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Ideal candidate has relevant treasury experience in fintech or financial institutions. Other relevant experience includes corporate treasury backgrounds with high operational complexity&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Capital market experience preferred&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Strong attention to detail and an obsession with driving operational improvements&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Creative problem solving and strong analytical skills, with the ability to handle ambiguity and make risk-based decisions&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;The ability and desire to grow the treasury team and successfully manage others&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Knowledge of capital markets, accounting, finance and tax&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Knowledge of appropriate treasury software packages&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Negotiation skills&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Presentation skills&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Strategic planning skills&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Verbal and written communication skills&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n&lt;div&gt;At Earnin, we believe that the best way to build a financial system that works for everyday people is by hiring a team that represents our diverse community. Our team is diverse not only in background and experience, but also in perspective. We celebrate our diversity and strive to create a culture of belonging. Earnin does not unlawfully discriminate on the basis of race, color, religion, sex (including pregnancy, childbirth, breastfeeding or related medical conditions), gender identity, gender expression, national origin, ancestry, citizenship, age, physical or mental disability, legally protected medical condition, family care status, military or veteran status, marital status, registered domestic partner status, sexual orientation, genetic information, or any other basis protected by local, state, or federal laws. Earnin is an E-Verify participant.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div&gt;Earnin does not accept unsolicited resumes from individual recruiters or third party recruiting agencies in response to job postings. No fee will be paid to third parties who submit unsolicited candidates directly to our hiring managers or HR team.&lt;/div&gt;', '2020-07-29 15:48:20'),
(167, '2263916', 'Earnin', 'VP of Brand', 'Marketing', 'Palo Alto, CA', 'http://platform_1.com/jobs/2263916', 'http://public-logo.com/activehours', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Earnin:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;Earnin is a community-supported financial platform with a suite of tools that let people take control of their financial future. Earnin started out by solving one of the greatest â€“ and least discussed â€“ inequities in the American financial system: the practice of employers paying workers bi-weekly. Earnin&#39;s core product, Cash Out, allows people to access the pay they&#39;ve already earned. There are no loans or hidden costs. People pay what they choose. Other products include: Balance Shield, which helps prevent overdrafts, a financial calendar that helps people budget and schedule payments, and Tip Yourself - a revolutionary free social savings app.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;Funding: Series C, current funding partners include Andreessen Horowitz, DST, Matrix Partners, Ribbit Capital, Felicis Ventures, and March Capital.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;Join us and help build a new financial system focused on fairness and peopleâ€™s needs.&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;You can help make a difference.&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;As VP of Brand youâ€™ll:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;ul&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Establish Earnin as the product and service that empowers people in the United States to reach their financial goals while relieving financial stress&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Position Earnin as a trusted financial advocate and ally for all Americans&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Build a meaningful emotional connection with community members and employees through a brand that in